@realmoney Jun 20, 2019 | 12:58 PM EDT DOUG KASS The Inflation Narrative Is Sheer Lunacy * Why are lower consumer prices a bad thing? * The U.S. situation is entirely different than the deflationary psychology causing problems in Japan.

* Our country's low inflation comes from productivity improvements in technology Deflation has definitely been turned into a bogeyman because of the experience of the Japanese. But Japan's problem wasn't the lack of inflation. That was just a symptom and, in fact,

low inflation has allowed its aging population to afford its cost of living. I fully recognize that the Fed is concerned that deflation is the default experience that would ensue if interest rates are not dropped and that economic growth is not catalyzed.
